				 																AWARD CEREMONY				 																																	 Today at G.D.Birla Sabhagar; 6.30pm: Pandit A.T. Kanan and Pandit Birju Maharaj will be honoured with the Haafiz Ali Khan Award. The award ceremony will be followed by a concert by the trio, Amaan Ali Bangash (sarod), Matthew Barley (cello) and Ayaan Ali Bangash (sarod). Organised by Sutanati Patakatha.				 																MUSIC				 																																	 December 24 at Kala Mandir; 6.30 pm: Sangit Kala Mandir presents a musical extravaganza featuring Sonu Nigam and his team.				 																																	 December 25 at Trincas; 8.30 pm: Shiva will perform on Blenders Pride Magical Nite.				 																																	 December 26 - 28 at Madhusudan Mancha: Ballygunge Maitreyee Music Circle presents the 6th Annual Sangeetacharya Radhika Mohan Maitreya Memorial Conference.				 																																	 December 26 at Science City; 6 pm: As part of TARAs Calcutta Festival 2003, a musical programme by Kabir Suman, Nachiketa and Shakila Jafar.				 																																	 December 27 at Science City; night-long: As part of Calcutta Festival 2003, a classical music programme featuring Pandit Jasraj, Pandit Hariprasad Chaurasia, Pandit Shivkumar Sharma, Begum Parveen Sultana, Ustad Rashid Khan, Sandipan Samajpati and Niladri Kumar. 				 																DANCE				 																																	 December 23 at Madhusudan Mancha; 7 pm: Jahnavi Centre for Performing Arts presents Madhuboni Chatterjee in the sixth show of her new dance choreography, Annya Aami (The Other Me), based on Tagores Chitrangada.				 																Art				 																																	 Till December 25 at Chemould Art Gallery: International Young Artists Organisation presents Senses  works by Anuswar, M. Ramachandran, Nandini Das, Madhumati Sen, Aditi Roy, Sumana Nath and Jnanesh Sekhar Ray.				 																																	 Till December 28 (except Monday) at Birla Academy of