ductivity.				 																EXHIBITION				 																																	 December 23 - 27 at Ramakrishna Mission Sikshanamandira amp; Vivekananda Sabhagriha, Belur Math: The ramakrishna Mission Sikshanamandira organises an education exhibition along with cultural programmes.				 																																	 Till December 24 at Sasha, 27 Mirza Ghalib Street; 11.30 am: Christmas Bazar showcasing items made by members of various NGOs including challenged children of Asha Niketan, destitute children of Don Bosco Asalayan and destitute women of Ashirwad. Also, studio ceramics by Ochre, a small unit in the interiors of Gujarat.				 																VARIETY				 																																	 Till December 26 at Bharatiyam Cultural Multiplex, Salt Lake; 2 pm: Christmas Mela 2003 with crafts fair, food festival, folk dances (6 pm onwards) and Odissi, Bharata Natyam and Kathakali recitals on Jesus Christ (on Dec. 25 amp; 26; 6 pm onwards).				 																																	 December 24 at Lake Land Country Club,off Kona Expressway; 9 pm onwards: Christmas Eve programme, Signature Wet n Wild, features belly dances Suzi (from Thailand) and Laila (from Russia) along with the dance troupe AbyBaby and fashion show by Calcutta models. Details at .				 																																	 December 24 - January 1 at FunCity; 10 am - 8 pm: Winter Carnival features live band, dance performance, magic show, various contest, food, etc.				 																																	 Till December 26 at Wot Not, 3, Ballygunge Park Road; 11.30 am - 2.30 pm amp; 4 pm - 6 pm: The fun super market ushers in the Christmas spirit with a 10-ft tall X-Mas tree and Santa Claus for company.				 																DRAMA				 																																	 Till December 26 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Nandikars 20th National Theatre Festival. Today: Jokumaraswamy (Kannad), directed by B.V. Karanth and produced by Benaka, Bangalore.				 																FELICITATION				 																								